data.title: Gloves Up, Crown Down
data.prompt: create a rap about winning a boxing championship
data.tags: hard-hitting, aggressive, bass-heavy, rap, with gritty synths and punchy drums
data.lyrics:
[Verse]
Steppin’ in the ring, gloves up, ready to clash
Fists like a storm, turn dreams to ash
Crowd’s on edge, feel the heat, no escape
Championship belt, it’s my name they drape

[Chorus]
Gloves up, crown down, I’m the king of the fight
Knockout power, lightin’ up the night
No one’s stoppin’ me, I’m claimin’ the throne
World champ vibes, I’m bad to the bone

[Verse 2]
Jab to the left, hook to the dome
Opponents crumble, sent back to their home
Sweat and blood, it’s the price of the game
Every punch I throw carves out my name

[Bridge]
Ring’s my kingdom, I’m the ruler, no doubt
One swing, lights out, hear the crowd shout
From the bottom to the top, I rose with the grind
Championship legacy, forever in my mind
